        "content": "<p>If you type hover your mouse over the name <code>mul_left_cancel₀</code>, you will see it is defined in Mathlib; if you then use \"Go to definition\" (that's keyboard shortcut F12 in my VScode), you will see its definition in Mathlib/Algebra/GroupWithZero/Defs.lean</p>\n<p>Essentially, it lets you cancel left-multiplication by a non-zero element: <code>theorem mul_left_cancel₀ (ha : a ≠ 0) (h : a * b = a * c) : b = c</code> (with some conditions).</p>",
